statement.p:
\textrm{A} = \left[\begin{array}{cc}
1 \amp 0\cr
-4 \amp 1
\end{array}\right] \left[\begin{array}{cc}
1 \amp -4\cr
0 \amp -2
\end{array}\right], \textbf{b}=\left[\begin{array}{c}
14\cr
-46
\end{array}\right]

solution.p:
SOLUTION: 
Solve L\mathbf{y} = \mathbf{b}, \left[\begin{array}{cc}
1 \amp 0\cr
-4 \amp 1
\end{array}\right] \mathbf{y} = \left[\begin{array}{c}
14\cr
-46
\end{array}\right], using back substitution, to obtain \mathbf{y} = \left[\begin{array}{c}
14\cr
10
\end{array}\right]. Now solve U \mathbf{x} = \mathbf{y}, \left[\begin{array}{cc}
1 \amp -4\cr
0 \amp -2
\end{array}\right] \mathbf{x} = \left[\begin{array}{c}
14\cr
10
\end{array}\right], using back substitution, to obtain \mathbf{x} = \left[\begin{array}{c}
-6\cr
-5
\end{array}\right].

